            As I pointed out, measures have been put in place by the chief electoral officer. I cannot give the Chamber a commitment that a Bill will be introduced
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_345wh' title='Col. 345WH &mdash; HC Deb 29 March 2001 vol 365 c345WH' name='column_345wh' href='#column_345wh' rel='bookmark'>345WH</a>
